HEADWORD: Tourbillion
<hw>Tour*bil"lion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>torbillion</ets> a whirlwind, tourbillion, fr. L. <ets>turbo</ets>,
-<ets>inis</ets>, a whirl, whirlwind.]</ety> <def>An ornamental firework
which turns round, when in the air, so as to form a scroll of
fire.</def> <rj><au>G. Francis.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

